```suggestion
that takes one iff statment instead of two implications. -/
```
Thanks for fixing this, this annoyed me already a few times but I was too lazy to fix it.

```suggestion
instance Dominant.isLocalAtTarget : IsLocalAtTarget @Dominant :=
``` 
we should agree on a convention and I think the tendency seems to be to put "standard properties" of a class of morphisms in an associated `<MorphismClass>.` namespace. So maybe put the whole section in `namespace Dominant`?

```suggestion
/-- A morphism of schemes is dominant if the underlying map has dense range. -/
```
I think it is safer to give the `RespectsIso` instance above a name and use it here.

```suggestion
that takes one iff statement instead of two implications. -/
```

It seems we have a majority of `Is...` in the algebraic geometry API:
```suggestion
class IsDominant : Prop where
```
Could you add that identities are dominant and get `IsMultiplicative` property?

```suggestion
  ⟨g.denseRange.comp f.denseRange g.base.2⟩
```
